title: For Sale:  NIB Kel-Tec PF-9 9MM Blued/Tan
postcontent:
I have a brand new Kel-Tec PF-9 9MM pistol for sale. This PF-9 has the flat dark earth frame with a blued slide. 

The PF-9 is a semi-automatic, locked breech pistol, chambered for the 9mm Luger cartridge. It has been developed from our highly successful P-11 and P-3AT pistols with maximum concealability in mind. The PF-9 has a single stack magazine holding 7 rounds. It is one of the lightest and flattest 9 mm ever made. Firing mechanism is Double-Action Only with an automatic hammer block safety. 

The PF-9 retains the best features from our P-11 and P-3AT pistols combined into the flattest and lightest single stack 9mm configuration ever made. The barrel, locking system, slide stop, assembly pin, front sight, recoil springs and guide rod are adapted from the P-11. The PF-9 is nearly identical to the P-11 in length and height and shares the same exterior controls. The shorter trigger system with integral hammer block and the extraction system are adapted from the P-3AT. Just like the P-11, the PF-9 will accept +P ammunition, however, not with continuous use.

 The rear sight is a new design and is adjustable for windage with the supplied allen wrench as well as for elevation with the use of shims (not included). The included 7 round rectangular magazine is supplied with a finger extension base plate and numbered holes. The under barrel accessory rail shares the dimensions of the MIL-STD-1913 picatinny rail although there is only one locking notch in the forward position.

title: For Sale:  NIB Kel-Tec P-3AT .380acp
postcontent:
I have a brand new Kel-Tec P-3AT .380acp handgun for sale. 

The P-3AT is a semi-automatic, locked breech pistol, chambered for the .380 Auto cartridge. It has been developed from our highly successful P-32 pistol with negligible increase in weight and size. The slidestop has been eliminated and the magazine capacity reduced to 6 rounds due to the larger cartridge. The firing mechanism is double action only. The magazine has a 6 round capacity. The KEL-TEC P-3AT is the lightest .380 Auto pistol ever made. Thanks to its locking dynamics and superior ergonometry, perceived recoil and practical accuracy are comparable to much larger guns. The P-3AT is mainly intended for plainclothes police officers as a secondary weapon, or for concealed carry by licensed citizens. The small grip size and light trigger pull make the P-3AT ideal for female shooters.

The P-3AT has five main component groups: barrel, slide, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 ordnance steel, heat treated to 48 HRC. The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor. The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer. The hammer is driven by a novel free floating extension spring. The light weight firing pin transmits the energy of the hammer to ignite the primer. After firing, the hammer block holds the hammer away from the firing pin, providing a mechanical safety.

title: For Sale:  1943 Lee Enfield Number 4 Mark 1, original and complete
postcontent:
1943 Lee Enfield Number 4 Mark 1, original and complete. pig-sticker bayo, bayo cover, sling and magazine.

Markings -

No.4.Mk1 - model and mark .  model number 4, mark 1

Seagull shaped V - stamp of acceptance. passed inspection. usually above factory and year mark, this stamp hit inbetween the factory and year mark.

M 1943 - factory and year. M indicates the Maltby royal ordnance factory in Maltby, England. year 1943. 

A G - serial number prefix. A G was the first prefix used early in 1943. A also indicates the gun was assembled using some non-standard parts from contractors. This means it was hand crafted and unique, so it will most likely have very little compatibility with standard rifles of the same model. G is a simple reference letter. 

13480 - serial number. range of 10000-19999. This rifle was the 3,481st of 10,000 in the A G prefix group.

Approximation -  This rifle was produced in February of 1943 at the Maltby royal ordnance factory. It was assembled by hand using the best parts available. The overall finish and appearance of the gun was secondary to the performance. It is one of a kind and shoots great. It may have been used in battle in 1943-1945.

title: For Sale/Trade:  2 Classic Handguns! Makarov & P-38. Buy separate or package deal!
postcontent:
1. $340. Walther P38 9mm Luger in great condition. It comes with one 8 round magazine. All matching numbers except for the magazine. I have shot around 50 rounds of Winchester white box through it and it functions flawlessly. This is a very accurate gun. Blueing is a little worn in places, but overall it is still in great condition. After WW2, from 1945 to 1957 no P38s were produced for the German military. However, when the newly formed "Bundeswehr" (German Defense Force) announced it wanted the P38 as its official service pistol, Walther resumed production of the P38 and the first ones were delivered to the West German military in June 1957. This particular gun was produced October 1957 (10/57 stamped) for the Bundeswehr. It bears the eagle markings and "BW" stamp.

2. $400. Russian Makarov. 9x18 Makarov. It comes with one 8 round magazine and 150rds of 9x18 ammo. IJ70-18A Made in Russia by IMEZ. IMEZ stands for Izhevskii Mechanicheskii Zavod or Izhevsk Mechanical Factory located in the city of Izhevsk near the Ural Mountains. They produce the Makarov, PSM, various shotguns, airguns, artificial pacemakers for the heart, oil drilling equipment. It is a goverment, state owned enterprise, but has the right to close its own business contracts and deals without govermental interferance.
Baikal is a foreign trade organization this is similar to North China Industries (NORINCO). This was a govermental organization that was used to market Soviet goods abroad. These days Baikal is hardly active in any trade with the US, largely because of the Bill Clinton imposed "voluntary trade restrictions." IMEZ used the grips with Baikal on it because...well, it was all they had.... Baikal also traded autos, trucks, various other consumer goods. Not only guns and ammo.

BUY BOTH FOR $600!
